entities.name: Action button
entities.description:
# Action button

Action buttons allow users to perform an action or mark a selection. They’re used for similar, task-based options within a workflow, and are ideal for interfaces where buttons aren’t meant to draw a lot of attention.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/action-button/)

languages.html:
<sp-action-group>
    <sp-action-button>
        <sp-icon slot="icon" size="xs" name="ui:Magnifier"></sp-icon>
        Button 1
    </sp-action-button>
    <sp-action-button>
        <sp-icon slot="icon" size="xs" name="ui:Magnifier"></sp-icon>
        Longer Button 2
    </sp-action-button>
    <sp-action-button>
        <sp-icon slot="icon" size="xs" name="ui:Magnifier"></sp-icon>
        Short 3
    </sp-action-button>
</sp-action-group>

entities.name: Action group
entities.description:
# Action group

An action group is a grouping of action buttons that are related to each other.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/action-group/)

entities.name: Button
entities.description:
# Button

Buttons allow users to perform an action or to navigate to another page. They have multiple styles for various needs, and are ideal for calling attention to where a user needs to do something in order to move forward in a flow.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/button/)

languages.javascriptreact:
<ButtonGroup>
  <Button variant="primary">Rate Now</Button>
  <Button variant="secondary">No, thanks</Button>
  <Button variant="secondary">Remind me later</Button>
</ButtonGroup>

entities.name: Button group
entities.description:
# Button group

A button group is a grouping of buttons whose actions are related to each other.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/button-group/)

entities.name: Checkbox
entities.description:
# Checkbox

Checkboxes allow users to select multiple items from a list of individual items, or to mark one individual item as selected.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/checkbox/)

languages.css:
Zoom in
Switch to the zoom tool then click and drag in the canvas to move your camera forward and backward.

entities.name: Coach mark
entities.description:
# Coach mark

Coach marks are temporary messages that educate users through new or unfamiliar product experiences. They can be chained into a sequence to form a tour.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/coach-mark/)

entities.name: Color area
entities.description:
# Color area

A color area allows users to visually select two properties of a color simultaneously. It's commonly used together with a color slider or color wheel.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/color-area/)

entities.name: Color slider
entities.description:
# Color slider

A color slider lets users visually change an individual channel of a color.

[View full documentation](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/color-slider/)
